## Key Tables
- `workflows` (per-run runtime.db) -- topic, config_hash, status
- `workflows_registry` (central `{run_root}/workflows_registry.db`) -- workflow_id, topic, config_hash, db_path, status, heartbeat_at
- `event_log` (per-run runtime.db) -- SSE event replay buffer; fields: workflow_id, event_type, payload, ts
- `cost_records` (per-run runtime.db) -- **single source of truth for all LLM call costs**; fields: workflow_id, model, phase, tokens_in, tokens_out, cost_usd, latency_ms, cache_read_tokens, cache_write_tokens; one row per LLM call written atomically by `src/llm/`; `/api/db/{run_id}/costs` and `_fetch_run_stats()` both read `SUM(cost_usd)` from here; `run_summary.json` total_cost is also derived from this table at finalize
- `study_cohort_membership` (per-run runtime.db) -- canonical included-study cohort ledger; one row per paper/workflow tracks screening_status, fulltext_status, synthesis_eligibility, exclusion_reason_code, source_phase; primary source for included-study counts (`included_primary`)
- `citations` (per-run runtime.db) -- fields: citekey, doi, title, authors, year, journal, bibtex, url, source_type; source_type values: 'included' (study from the review), 'methodology' (PRISMA/RoB/GRADE method papers), 'background_sr' (background systematic reviews cited in Introduction); source_type is used to split the CITATION CATALOG into separate labeled blocks for the writing LLM

